{"key":"processedPost-18381847","value":{"id":18381847,"first":18381689,"last":18382030,"when":1370608242,"utime":"06/07/13 03:30 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Activeimagination said:</strong><br />I did use a cloth at the bottom of the pot while sterilizing but this didn't seem to help, any suggestions on how to avoid this?</blockquote><br />Yes.&nbsp; Don't use a cloth.&nbsp; A wet cloth has an R factor of zero.&nbsp; <br />Use a trivet, perlite, rocks, foil, jar lids, or anything else which will elevate the jars off the bottom so water can flow under them.&nbsp; You can see a proved, recommended method of elevating the jars off the bottom in the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek videos</a>.<br />RR"}}